Request focus is only for the views not for the primitive data types.
For the Textview to keep in focus by using XML or programmatically,

    // Parent view
    LinearLayout ll = …
    final int childCount = ll.getChildCount();
    for (int i = 0; i &lt; childCount; i++) {
      View v = ll.getChildAt(i);
      // Check is v is instanceof TextView.
    }

Xml attributes,

    // Based on the requirement
    android:focusable=&quot;true&quot;
    android:focusableInTouchMode = &quot;true&quot;


Programmatically,

    TextView text = view.findViewById(R.id.textView);
    text.requestFocus();

**requestFocus** is for a **View** like **EditText**, not a **string**. You can use it like this:

    textview.requestFocus();
or
    `&lt;TextView...&gt;
        &lt;requestFocus /&gt;
    &lt;/TextView&gt;`

