This thing is called **Short Circuit Evaluation**. Basically JS logical operators are evaluated from ***left to right***. This feature comes handy when you want to assign some value to a variable based on the `OR or AND` logic. For examples

    true || true;
    // true
    true || false;
    // true
    false || false;
    // false

Here if the left statement is `true` then it will not check the right side condition &amp; return that left side value this is called short circuit evaluation.

For more information read this https://codeburst.io/javascript-what-is-short-circuit-evaluation-ff22b2f5608c

